notesStmt.note: Some folios damaged, restored on paper.
On folio 79r are four short midrashic passages on Deuteronomy.
A note of sale, dated 2028 (1717), between Ya῾akov ben Se῾id ibn Daud and Yehosaf ben Se῾adia ben Avraham ben Mosheh: folio 1r.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Midrash ha-gadol on Exodus, attributed to David Adani.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 ; ruled lines: 38; written lines: 38; Has some marginal notes and additions. Mem and shin are truncated in the lines. Beginnings of new chapters are written in larger characters. Folio 15v should be read after 16r.
